---
import PageLayout from "../layouts.astro/PageLayout.astro";
import "../style/style.css";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="tourguide">
  <header></header>
  <body>
    <section class="tourguide">
      <div>
        <h1>COPENHAGEN TOURGUIDE -</h1>
        <div class="tofrom">
          <h1>FROM: CREATIVE LOCALS</h1>
          <h1>T0: CREATIVE INDIVIDUALS</h1>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <p class="underoverskrift">Multimedia designers Louise Bonde, Marie Green, Sarah Neiiendam & Thomas Palmer take you on a journey through Copenhagen's creative corners, vibrant culture, and local hangouts.</p>
        <img class="foto" src="/glypto.webp" alt="glypto" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <h3>Glyptoteket: Where Art and Atmosphere Meet</h3>
        <p>
          Step into Copenhagen's Glyptotek, a sunlit oasis where ancient sculptures, classic paintings, and modern art share the same space. As you wander through the airy halls, pause at hidden corners, marvel at intricate details, or simply soak up the calm, inspiring atmosphere. Don't forget to peek into the winter garden, where natural light turns every sculpture into a glowing masterpiece. Need a break? The museum's cozy café is perfect for a coffee or light bite, and the souvenir shop offers charming keepsakes to remember your visit. Glyptoteket is open Tuesday to Sunday, 11 AM-6 PM, and tickets cost 120 DKK for adults (children and students often free). Whether you're an art lover, a curious traveler, or just looking for a serene escape in the city, Glyptoteket is a place to
          explore, linger, and get inspired—where every corner tells a story and every visit feels a little like discovering Copenhagen all over again.
        </p>
        <button>VISIT HERE →</button>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <img class="foto" src="/dac.webp" alt="dac" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <h3>DAC: A Playground for Ideas</h3>
        <p>
          At DAC, architecture feels alive. Sunlight glances off miniature cityscapes, shadows play across intricate models, and interactive installations invite you to touch, tilt, and turn ideas into something tangible. Each corner tells a story—of buildings, neighborhoods, and the city itself—helping you see Copenhagen not just as it is, but as it could be. The rooftop café offers coffee, light bites, and a sweeping view of the harbor, where the city's lines and shapes become part of the inspiration. The shop downstairs holds books, clever design objects, and souvenirs that capture Danish creativity to take home. DAC is open Tuesday to Sunday, 11 AM-6 PM, with adult tickets around 120 DKK. It's a space that invites curiosity, challenges your perspective, and leaves you noticing the
          shapes, lines, and ideas shaping the world long after you've left.
        </p>
        <button>VISIT HERE →</button>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="grid_1-1">
          <img class="foto" src="/kaffe.webp" alt="kaffe" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <img class="foto" src="/3x_kaffe.webp" alt="3x_kaffe" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>
        <h3>Lido: A Cozy Copenhagen Hideaway</h3>
        <p>
          Tucked away on Vester Voldgade, Lido is a hidden gem where Copenhagen slows down just enough for you to catch your breath. With warm interiors, fresh pastries, light bites, and perfectly brewed coffee, it's a favorite for locals, creatives, and anyone looking for a quiet corner to sketch, scroll, or brainstorm. The vibe is effortlessly relaxed, with the kind of charm that makes you linger longer than planned. A cappuccino costs around 50 DKK, pastries from 40 DKK, and the café is open Monday to Friday, 8 AM-4 PM, and weekends 9 AM-4 PM—perfect for early morning inspiration or a midday reset. Lido isn't just about coffee; it's a space where ideas flow as easily as the drinks, a small creative sanctuary in the heart of the city. Whether you're on a gallery hop, meeting friends, or
          just seeking a pause, it's the kind of spot that makes Copenhagen feel a little more magical.
        </p>
        <button>VISIT HERE →</button>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="grid_1-1">
          <img class="foto" src="/flag.webp" alt="flag" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <img class="foto" src="/art_gallery.webp" alt="art_gallery" width="600" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>
        <h3>Christiania: Where Freedom Lives</h3>
        <p>
          Christiania isn't just a place — it's a feeling. Step inside the gates and the city's rules seem to fade away. Colorful murals stretch across walls, music drifts from hidden corners, and every street feels alive with stories, creativity, and possibility. Here, bikes replace cars, gardens bloom in unexpected spaces, and people live life on their own rhythm. Wander through the winding streets and discover tiny cafés, art studios, and handmade shops, each with its own vibe and energy. The air hums with creativity—street performers, sculptors, painters, and musicians all carving out their own worlds. It's a place where imagination isn't just celebrated; it's the law. Come to Christiania not just to see it, but to feel it. Grab a coffee, sit by the water, watch the sunset over the old
          warehouses, and let the freedom of the place inspire your own ideas. Every corner has a story, every wall a splash of color, and every person a spark of inspiration. Christiania invites you to slow down, look closer, and leave with your head buzzing with creativity—and maybe a little piece of its free-spirited magic tucked into your heart.
        </p>
        <button>VISIT HERE →</button>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
  <Footer />
</PageLayout>
